[
    {
        "content": "<p>/poll Which of these is called <code>lift_comp_ι</code>?</p>\n<ul>\n<li>lift (g ∘ ι) = g</li>\n<li>(lift f) ∘ ι = f</li>\n</ul>",
        "id": 533873683,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1754949214
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>And of course the more important question, what should the other one be called?</p>",
        "id": 533873812,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1754949260
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>We have precedent here, but the precedent is to call the other one <code>ι_comp_lift</code>, which is definitely not a reasonable reading of the naming guide.</p>",
        "id": 533874036,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1754949349
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>can you give some examples?</p>",
        "id": 533875657,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1754949947
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I'm having trouble inferring the types in <code>lift (g ∘ ι) = g</code></p>",
        "id": 533875741,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1754949984
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>oh I figured it out</p>",
        "id": 533875878,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1754950039
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>g : BigHom (F X) Y</code>, <code>f : LittleHom X Y</code>, <code>ι : LittleHom X (F X)</code></p>",
        "id": 533875885,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1754950042
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I guess strictly speaking <code>(lift f) ∘ ι = f</code> is actually <code>(lift f).toLittleHom.comp ι = f</code>, which maybe solves the naming issue</p>",
        "id": 533876016,
        "sender_full_name": "Eric Wieser",
        "timestamp": 1754950118
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><code>lift_app_comp_ι</code> would be the other one <span aria-label=\"smile\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f604\" role=\"img\" title=\"smile\">:smile:</span></p>",
        "id": 533878906,
        "sender_full_name": "Kenny Lau",
        "timestamp": 1754952084
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"310045\">Eric Wieser</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Naming.20of.20universal.20property.20lemmas/near/533876016\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I guess strictly speaking <code>(lift f) ∘ ι = f</code> is actually <code>(lift f).toLittleHom.comp ι = f</code>, which maybe solves the naming issue</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Strictly speaking <code>lift (g ∘ ι)</code> is actually <code>lift (g.toLittleHom.comp ι)</code></p>",
        "id": 533879403,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1754952379
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>but sometimes <code>LittleHom</code> and <code>BigHom</code> are the same type</p>",
        "id": 533879584,
        "sender_full_name": "Aaron Liu",
        "timestamp": 1754952490
    },
    {
